##A video blogger's view of Wuhan

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

"In the face of the plague, thank you for letting us see the beauty and kindness in human nature" , "you let us see a real Wuhan. " The word that appears most in the comments is "true. ".

At seven o'clock in the evening in Wuhan, the streets were empty, and every now and then 120 ambulances sped by.

Wen | from the Beijing News, Xie Lei

Editor | Hu Jie proofread | Li Lijun

This article is about 4347 words long and takes about 8 minutes to read

Spider monkey bread, a name that's been popping up in internet searches lately.

The name came from what his band friends called him, probably because of the little prince, plus the Baobab tree he'd met on the trip, and then when he changed his online name, the words spider monkey bread popped into his head.

Spider was originally a freelance film and television workers, because of the filming of the pneumonia period Wuhan diary, just over 10 days, his Weibo fans from more than 10,000 to more than 2.3 million. The documentary video, which was renamed Wuhan Diary 2020 from Wuhan Fengcheng Diary, has now been updated to the eighth episode and has become a window for many people to understand the current situation in Wuhan.

The video has also been uploaded to Youtube, attracting attention from many netizens at home and abroad. There are greetings from overseas Chinese from Australia, Austria, Canada and Indonesia, support written in Korean, and blessings from many friends from Hong Kong and Taiwan.

In the spider's shot, there are people lost on the street with suitcases that can't go home, there are sanitation workers who wear masks to keep working, there are delivery men who still ride motorcycles on the road, there are medical workers who struggle on the front lines, there were hotel volunteers who provided free accommodation for medical staff, and there were grandfathers who took advantage of the sunshine to come out and play Tai Chi.

One Taiwanese netizen wrote that the most important thing he wanted to do after the outbreak was to go from Taiwan to Wuhan to find Mr. Spider Monkey bread, have a meal together, have a cup of tea, chat, and see the beautiful scenery of Wuhan.

Back to the scene in Wuhan, where eight bottles of anti-aids drugs are being sold from house to house as part of a nationwide fund-raising drive for HIV infected people

The warmth of an epidemic

On February 5, the 12th day of the 1st Lunar Month, the 14th day of Wuhan's closing of the Han corridor, Huoshenshan hospital admitted the second batch of new pneumonia patients. The streets are sparsely populated, with 120 emergency vehicles racing past from time to time, before returning to a long silence.

For the first time in more than 10 days, the spider cooked a decent meal at home. It tasted just like mother's. Since the shooting of Wuhan Diary on January 23, spiders go out early and come back late every day. They often cut the film until dawn and eat only one or two meals a day.

The spider was born and raised in Wuhan, and this is thirty-seven of his years in the city. He has been used to living alone for more than ten years. Last year, my mother went to Australia to live with my sister. This Spring Festival, the girlfriend in Hainan had originally planned to come to Wuhan to live with spiders, but the sudden outbreak of disease and city control completely disrupted the plan.

It was twenty-nine o 'clock in the morning on New Year's Day, and spider was still awake. He was almost the first to know about the notice of "closing the city. " . "there was a bit of foreboding before, and I felt as soon as the news came out that it had actually happened. "

The spider didn't immediately decide to film. "I'm actually in a panic, afraid of going out at this time will not be at risk, will not be infected with the virus. " After some hesitation, plus has not gone out for several days. The next morning, the spider decided to go out and buy supplies and supplies, and record the city with the GOPRO camera at hand.

Spider said that the first day of shooting is very careful, mostly in the car facing outside, and sometimes even did not open the window. It was this short two-minute video, posted on the Internet, quickly attracted the eyes of thousands of netizens. It is the first time to record the scene after the closure of Wuhan, when the rain gloomy sky, deserted streets, closed business mall, as well as masks can not see the expression of the face.

At seven o'clock in the evening in Wuhan, the streets are empty, and every now and then 120 emergency vehicles rush past, before returning to the long silence.

As they went out more and more, they came into contact with different people, and their fears were gradually overcome. He decided to use his own eyes to record and witness the siege of the city. To let the outside world and the people in Wuhan, to understand the real side of Wuhan, to eliminate the panic, this was his original intention to shoot.

In more than 10 days of shooting, there is one scene that the spider most unforgettable. He was stopping to photograph the closed Yangtze River Tunnel when he saw two elderly men coming from a distance. The woman had white hair, wore a mask, sat in a wheelchair and carried a large bag of groceries in her lap. The old man was wearing a baseball cap, a sweaty forehead, a brown knit shirt, a stripped jacket clutched in his wheelchair, and two carry-on bags strapped to his armrest. There was no traffic on the wide road, and the spider caught sight of the figure pushing the cart.

He learned that the two men, both in their 70s, had been released from the hospital. My Grandmother, who has diabetes, was admitted to the hospital at the age of twenty-eight. She bought food from the supermarket every day. Life was very inconvenient. She wanted to go home for a long time, but she never got in touch with the help car. Her children were in Hankou, and the car was banned. Today they insisted on leaving the hospital, ten kilometers away, GRANDPA decided to spend three hours to push grandma home.

An elderly man tried to wheel his family home in Wuhan for three hours.

When the spider met them, the old man had been walking for more than an hour, about a third of the way. "almost there, " the grandfather gasped.

Then the spider sent the two old man home, before leaving the old man wearing a mask waved goodbye to him.

"This is the most moving scene I have seen since I shot the castle. " The spider's voice becomes very soft.

The spider was also moved by a team volunteer named Kayley Chung, a young mother. There were three children, the oldest was 13 and the third was only 4. After settling her three children in the morning, she set off from home at about eleven o'clock and went to the volunteer group to deliver supplies. She didn't get home for dinner until eight or nine in the evening.

"I hope Wuhan can get back to normal as soon as possible. Now we can do our best to help. These materials are hard to get now. We'll pay for the gas. It's nothing, " Kayley Chung said with a laugh. She protected herself well for the sake of the child.

The spider followed her all afternoon, and in the evening, Kayley Chung called the children and told the boss to make noodles for her younger siblings from the dishes she had washed before she left. She's on the phone, giving the boss a little guidance on how to get down.

Volunteer Kayley Chung calls the kids and instructs the boss to make noodles for the younger siblings.

Later, during the video chat, the spider saw that the children were enjoying themselves at home and had eaten all the noodles. Kayley Chung let out a hoot and gave Leah an I told you so look. She said she would remain a volunteer until no one in Wuhan wears a mask anymore.

"that moment I feel particularly moving, very insipid, but very stab heart, " said the spider.

From chronicler to volunteer

As a film and television workers, the main task of the spider is objective shooting and recording. But with more and more people and things to see, in such a big environment where everyone is helping each other, spiders are also deeply infected, hoping to do something. "Now that the city is closed, the entire population of the city is a community of destiny, and everyone has to fight the epidemic together. "

Back to the scene: Wuhan "Doctor Station" DILEMMA: Disinfection Water and other supplies shortage, private goods vehicles into the city blocked.

He joined a group of volunteers who drove medical staff to and from work. On New Year's Eve, he got up at around 7:00 in the morning, wearing a disposable medical mask, and received a doctor of facial features. The doctor got on the bus with a plastic bag, saying that the Spring Festival holiday for all medical staff had been cancelled, "We all take instant noodles to New Year's Eve dinner. "

The paramedics told him that they, too, felt a lot of warmth. A co-worker said she needed N95 masks, so a neighbor gave her the few she had. And a co-worker said she needed goggles, and the next day, someone put them on the door.

A paramedic gave spider an N95 mask as she got off the bus. "We use surgical masks in our department, " she said. "You work so hard, but you still need this. "

A paramedic drops spider off with an N95 mask.

After each paramedic gets out of the car, the spider disinfects the seat with alcohol spray and then wipes it with paper. In comments, he was told to wait for the alcohol to evaporate, to wear gloves, to press down the wire over his mask and to keep pressure on the bridge of his nose.

Spider said, and many people said to send a mask to their own. He received a mask from the lead singer of the Chinese Footblall band, and at the end of the third episode, he inserted a song written for Wuhan by the Chinese Footblall band, "people, AH, full of hope, what's on the other side of the darkness, will have a life far away. "

SPIDERS are also involved in delivering drugs to patients. That batch of drugs is in the fourth and fifth HMO treatment of cleats, originally a treatment for AIDS antiviral drug. One person, who goes by the online name HIV squirrel, has been volunteering to collect and distribute AIDS drugs.

After Squirrel saw the spider's video, he was contacted by a friend to help deliver the drug to the patient, out of trust. It's the first time a spider has been in contact with a patient or family member, and it's a difficult thing to do at this particular time. The spider would call to make an appointment, drop the drug off at a designated location, and watch the patient pick it up before leaving.

The spider drives the car and dispenses medicine to the patient.

During the course of delivering the Medicine, he saw that the patient did not reach a state of loss of control as claimed. On the contrary, everyone was strong and actively trying to deal with the disease.

One of the girls, spider very impressed, received a phone call that there are drugs, she almost cried. It wasn't the first time spider had come to a hospital to ask for help. She fought tooth and nail for the paramedics to save her dad. The girl told the spider that she had cried her eyes out.

Behind the camera, the spider struggles to hold back tears. "Only the people and families who have been through this really understand this helplessness and pain. "

"We all know there are a lot of tough people and regrets out there, but we have to keep hope alive, " spider said.

The people in the spider's Web.

I used to cry during the editing

Since the launch of the Wuhan Diary, the lives of spiders have changed dramatically.

Before the outbreak, he was more casual, his own cooking, hand coffee, teasing the cat, walking the dog, cutting the film. But after January 23, he seemed to wind up, and while everyone else was at home, the spider was too busy to eat.

For the first few days, the spider would go out every morning at 7 or 8 a.m. to film, stuff a few things before heading out the door, or make a simple grab cake with Bacon in it, all of which were instant family meals. Half way to eat some dry food hungry, outside the restaurant is basically closed. I'd come back at 90:00 in the evening, sometimes as early as 4:00 or 5:00. Clothes, hats, and masks are removed and placed in a room, sanitized with ultraviolet light, and camera equipment is left in the car, not taken home.

Every night back home, the cat and dog will take turns to run to the spider side, welcome back after a hard day of filming the owner. The dog would lie on his lap, and the cat would crouch beside the computer, looking curiously at the image on the screen.

The first few days were exhausting. Because want to send out video in time, spider general meeting is in turn, cut a piece to cut until 4 or 5 o'clock in the morning. Get Two or three more hours of sleep, then go out the next day and shoot again.

When he got home at four in the morning, he found that the pots and pans had not been washed for two days. In the past, dishes and chopsticks had never stayed overnight. "It seems that I need to embrace life again, " the spider wrote on Weibo.

"My friends say I'm on a high and I'm not tired or hungry. But when I stop, I get really tired. "

Wuhan lights up the banks of the Yangtze River every night.

Both his girlfriend in Hainan and his mother and sister in Australia were worried about spiders, but the family knew that if a spider wanted to do something, he would do it. "I've done a lot of things that looked dangerous to them before, like going to Africa and India by myself. They understood that, even though it wasn't supportive. They just told me to be careful. "

In 2017, spiders entered the film business. He's been shooting and editing on his own for a long time, and he's developed his own process. Before filming the Wuhan Diary, spiders were making short films about their travels. "lost in Madagascar" , "Indian motorcycle ride" , "Nepal travels" are all his works on the road. Traveling spiders, dark-skinned, with mustaches, wearing local clothes, and friends met on the road to play happily, optimistic, positive, full of life.

Unlike previous travel diaries, spider said he was observing people and society from his own point of view and was much more calm and restrained, but incorporated into his feelings about the world.

Spider never thought he'd be famous. On the day of the release of the second film, the number of fans jumped to more than 60,000. And told a lot of my friends that the fan base was growing too fast. What he didn't think at the time was that in ten days'time, his followers would grow to over two million.

He occasionally joked about the surge in followers in his circle of friends, but he knew it was temporary and that when it was over, things would go back to the way they were.

In fact, the spider did not think to shoot for a long time at first, but then the film attracted so many people's attention, people want to see through his lens now Wuhan, and some people feel the warmth and encouragement from these videos. All of these became his responsibility and motivation to keep filming.

"In this world, all human nature is magnified, good and evil are magnified. " Spider saw too many helpless people in the street, too many unhappy families and sad tears. He had no idea what was happening to them and could not imagine their situation.

"There are always many people who say that Wuhan people are hot-tempered, and I don't deny that. " Although born and raised in Wuhan, spiders didn't have much regional pride in the city. He loved to travel, went to many places, and even moved to other places several times. But this time, he saw a different side of Wuhan herself -- a strong, lovely, warm-hearted, united person. "I was restrained in the video, but when I edited it, I cried a lot. "

"I seem to have rediscovered the city, and I think I love Wuhan even more now. "

Spider said he seems to re-recognize the city, now more love Wuhan.

Like everyone else, the spider's best hope now is an early end to the outbreak. He has been waiting for the end of the day, said his girlfriend, she will be the first time to find him, the future day, with him in Wuhan live together.
